issue.body:
Below is a cabal project config:

```yaml

    default-extensions: ConstraintKinds
                      , FlexibleContexts
                      , NoImplicitPrelude
                      , OverloadedStrings
                      , QuasiQuotes
                      , TemplateHaskell

    -- other-modules:
    -- other-extensions:
    build-depends:    base >= 4.19.0.0
                    , katip 
                    , text
                    , digestive-functors 
                    , digestive-functors-aeson
                    , string-random 
                    , mtl
                    , data-has
                    , classy-prelude
                    , pcre-heavy

                    , time-lens
                    , resource-pool
                    , postgresql-simple
                    , exceptions
                    , postgresql-migration
                    , extra

                    , aeson
                    , lifted-base
                    , scotty
                    , http-types
                    , cookie
                    , wai

                    , blaze-builder

    hs-source-dirs:   src
    default-language: GHC2021
```

execution vulnerability. Furthermore, popular forges like GitHub do not

src/Text/Digestive/Aeson.hs:88:56: error: [GHC-83865]
    • Couldn't match type ‘T.Text’ with ‘Data.Aeson.Key.Key’
      Expected: Index (Data.Aeson.KeyMap.KeyMap Value)
        Actual: T.Text
    • In the first argument of ‘at’, namely ‘p’
      In the second argument of ‘(.)’, namely ‘at p’
      In the second argument of ‘(.)’, namely ‘_Object . at p’
   |
88 |     pathElem p = maybe (non (object []) . _Object . at p)

Error: [Cabal-7125]
Failed to build digestive-functors-aeson-1.1.27 (which is required by exe:practical-web-dev-ghc from practical-web-dev-ghc-0.1.0.0). See the build log above for details.

The complete project is on [github branch c07]( https://github.com/rajcspsg/practical-web-dev-ghc/tree/c07).

Seems like `digestive-functors-aeson` is pretty outdated.

issue.title: A working example of FreeIPA in Kubernetes 1.26
issue.body:
Hi,

After searching for current examples of working Kubernetes manifests that I could use to deploy FreeIPA in my home lab I ended up having to piece one together from a number of posts and repos. I thought it would be good for me to document what I learned.

I'm [deploying FreeIPA as a StatefulSet](https://github.com/iPenguin/bare-metal-kubernetes/blob/master/roles/freeipa/templates/freeipa-statefulset.yaml.j2) with a MetalLB [LoadBalancer in front of it](https://metallb.universe.tf/](https://github.com/iPenguin/bare-metal-kubernetes/blob/master/roles/freeipa/templates/freeipa-lb.yaml.j2)).

The biggest thing I found missing in all the examples I saw was the need for a `startupProbe`. This block prevents the pod from being killed during the long startup on initial install (15+ minutes) without adversely impacting pod restarts.

```
  startupProbe:
    httpGet:
      path: /
      port: 80
    failureThreshold: 35
    periodSeconds: 30
``` 

I hope someone else finds this helpful.
-Brian

comment.body:
Hello,
First of all, thank you so much for your great and active community!

I'm writing in reference to the manifest that user @iPenguin  kindly shared earlier.
 I tried deploying the manifest myself, and I encountered a problem during restart named service in install phase — it fails unless I set privileged: true.

When I do set privileged: true, everything works well and the installation completes successfully. However, after a pod restart, the hostname changes, and the FreeIPA service fails to start correctly.

I checked the logs of the named service, and it fails with a systemd start service timeout, which seems to be the root cause

Here are a few additional details about my environment:

    Kubernetes version: 1.29.5

    OS: Rocky Linux 9.4

    SELinux: Disabled

I’ve tried the following to troubleshoot:

    Used different base images like Rocky and CentOS.

    Set the IPA_SERVER_IP environment variable explicitly in the relevant container.
    
    Remove And Modify  securityContext Section

Unfortunately, none of these changes resolved the issue.

I'm wondering if there is any document or recommended approach for handling this scenario — especially how  run the pod successfully without privileged mode.

Below is my current manifest: 

```yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: freeipa
spec:
  selector:
    app: freeipa
  clusterIP: 10.233.5.115
  ports:
  - name: http
    port: 80
    targetPort: 80
  - name: https
    port: 443
    targetPort: 443
  - name: dns-tcp
    port: 53
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 53
  - name: dns-udp
    port: 53
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 53
  - name: kerberos-tcp
    port: 88
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 88
  - name: kerberos-udp
    port: 88
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 88
  - name: kpasswd-tcp
    port: 464
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 464
  - name: kpasswd-udp
    port: 464
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 464
  - name: ldap
    port: 389
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 389
  - name: ldaps
    port: 636
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 636
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: freeipa
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: freeipa
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: freeipa
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: freeipa-container
          image: freeipa/freeipa-server:rocky-9 # almalinux , centos  
          resources:
            requests:
              memory: "5Gi"
              cpu: "2"
            limits:
              memory: "5Gi"
              cpu: "2"
          imagePullPolicy: Always
          env:
            - name: IPA_SERVER_HOSTNAME
              value: freeipa.freetest.freeipame
            - name: IPA_SERVER_INSTALL_OPTS
              value: --unattended --realm=FREETEST.FREEIPAME --domain freetest.freeipame --ip-address=10.233.5.115 -p P@ssw0rd!@# -a P@ssw0rd!@# --no-forwarders --ssh-trust-dns --setup-dns --no-ntp 
          securityContext:
            capabilities:
              add: 
                - SYS_TIME
                - NET_BIND_SERVICE
            seccompProfile:
              type: Unconfined
          volumeMounts:
            - name: freeipa-server-data
              mountPath: /data
            - name: cgroups
              mountPath: /sys/fs/cgroup
            - name: run
              mountPath: /run
            - name: tmp
              mountPath: /tmp
            - mountPath: /dev/shm
              name: dshm
      volumes:
        - name: cgroups
          hostPath:
            path: /sys/fs/cgroup
        - name: run
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
        - name: tmp
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
        - name: dshm
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
            sizeLimit: 5Gi
        - name: freeipa-server-data
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: freeipa-server-data

```
Thanks in advance for your support and guidance

pull_request.body:
Bumps [sass](https://github.com/sass/dart-sass) from 1.87.0 to 1.88.0.
Release notes

Sourced from sass's releases.

Dart Sass 1.88.0

To install Sass 1.88.0, download one of the packages below and add it to your PATH, or see the Sass website for full installation instructions.

Changes

  • Allow custom properties with empty values (such as --var:;).

  • Fix a bug when calculating source spans for interpolations.

Dart and JS APIs

  • Potentially breaking bug fix: Throw an error when passing a function or mixin object from one compilation to another.

Dart API

  • Deprecate passing a relative URL to compileString() and related functions.

See the full changelog for changes in earlier releases.

Changelog

pull_request.title: Fix import paths and add Xvfb dependencies for CI
pull_request.body:
# Fix CI Tests by Making pywin32 Dependency Conditional

## Description
This PR fixes the failing CI tests by making the pywin32 dependency conditional on the Windows platform. The CI was failing because it was trying to install pywin32 on Ubuntu Linux, which is not supported.

## Changes
- Modified requirements.txt to make pywin32 dependency conditional on Windows platform using the platform_system marker

## Testing
- No local testing was performed as specified in the task
- CI should now pass on all Python versions (3.9, 3.10, 3.11)

issue.title: Bug Report: Crash When Launching BlueStacks – SetForegroundWindow Invalid Handle
issue.body:
**Environment:**
- **Python version:** 3.11
- **OS:** Windows 11
- **Script:** `auto_pokemon_tcgp.py`
- **Location:** Line 239 in `launch_game()` function

---

### 💥 Description:

When running the script with:

```bash
py -3.11 auto_pokemon_tcgp.py
```
The script attempts to launch BlueStacks and then crashes with the following output:
```
Starting Auto Pokemon TCGP...

None of the BlueStacks processes are running. Launching...
Restarting py script

Starting Auto Pokemon TCGP...

BlueStacks is running
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "auto_pokemon_tcgp.py", line 1041, in <module>
    main()
  File "auto_pokemon_tcgp.py", line 172, in main
    launch_game()
  File "auto_pokemon_tcgp.py", line 239, in launch_game
    win32gui.SetForegroundWindow(HWND)
pywintypes.error: (1400, 'SetForegroundWindow', 'Invalid window handle.')

```
